<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 2:36PM EST  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Slick Travel Conditions this Afternoon...
A brief period of wet, heavy snow will cause roads to become slick
this afternoon. Accidents have been reported across the area.
Accumulations of 1 to 3 inches are expected...especially north of
highway 30. Anyone travelling this afternoon should leave extra
time to reach your destination and remember to take it slow on ice
and snow. The snow will diminish from west to east between 3 and
6 PM EST.</description>
